Speaker 1: Okay, I see the doctor has you on refills every two months, which you do not have to have.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: That way it keeps your prescription active and just allows you to call in whenever you need a refill.

Speaker 1: And then if you don't need one by then, you just call and pause it further.

Speaker 2: I can pause that for you until July 31st of 2026.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I just want to cancel the whole thing.

Speaker 2: I don't want to be billed anymore for any more prescriptions.

Speaker 1: Okay, not a problem.

Speaker 2: Okay, I went ahead and canceled you out. You're all set.
